# Copy to .env and fill in. .env is gitignored — never commit real secrets.
# Flow: docker compose up -d  →  log in once (claude auth login)  →  done.
# Every other setting is loaded from this file.

# ===== REQUIRED =====
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:put-your-botfather-token-here
OWNER_ID=<your-telegram-user-id>

# ===== Auth =====
# PRIMARY way: log in interactively once; creds are stored on the volume
# (/data/.claude) and survive restarts — nothing needs to go in .env:
#   docker exec -it -u botuser <container> claude auth login
# (You MUST use -u botuser so the creds belong to the user the bot runs as.)
#
# Alternative (headless, no interactive login) — uncomment one of these:
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=sk-ant-oat-...   # create with: claude setup-token
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...             # pay-per-token

# ===== Permission mode =====
# auto = Auto Mode (classifier-gated): auto-runs ROUTINE tasks without prompting, but still
#   BLOCKS risky/outbound/irreversible actions. Doesn't hang headless. → RECOMMENDED for bots.
# Modes: auto | default | acceptEdits | bypassPermissions | plan.
PERMISSION_MODE=auto
# acceptEdits = auto-approves FILE EDITS only; STILL prompts on every Bash/network command →
#   lots of nagging accepts.
# bypassPermissions (auto-runs EVERY tool without prompting): Claude Code 2.1.126+ requires a
#   one-time "Yes, I accept" dialog every launch — it can't be skipped headless → the bot
#   HANGS. You'd have to accept by hand:
#   docker exec -it -u botuser <bot> tmux attach -t claude  → ↓ pick "Yes, I accept" → Enter → Ctrl+B D

# ===== Specialized bot (role profile) =====
# BOT_ROLE = boot the bot into a role in the delivery workflow. On first run the entrypoint
#   seeds the role's CLAUDE.md + settings + rules (layered ON TOP of the base CLAUDE.md —
#   it does not override the base security/isolation). Values: ba | planner | dev-fe | dev-be | tester.
#   EMPTY / unset / default = DEFAULT BEHAVIOR, UNCHANGED (existing bots are unaffected).
#   Details: roles/README.md.
# BOT_ROLE=ba

# ===== Optional =====
# MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
# TZ=Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh
# WORK_DIR=/working-directory/claude-telegram-bot   # where claude runs (pre-trusted)
